1
00:00:01,334 --> 00:00:03,336
[♪ theme music playing]

2
00:00:29,112 --> 00:00:30,196
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

3
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:34,826
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

4
00:00:34,909 --> 00:00:36,202
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

5
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:37,287
[Haran] Huh?

6
00:00:37,370 --> 00:00:39,039
{\an8}EPISODE 11

7
00:00:39,622 --> 00:00:40,623
{\an8}[chuckles softly]

8
00:00:55,138 --> 00:00:57,974
{\an8}THANKS FOR THE

9
00:01:14,240 --> 00:01:16,076
[♪ dramatic music playing]

10
00:01:16,159 --> 00:01:17,410
{\an8}Kang Hyeokchan…

11
00:01:17,494 --> 00:01:19,662
{\an8}KANG HYEOKCHAN
GLASS TUBE

12
00:01:20,455 --> 00:01:22,624
{\an8}Why is this name here?

13
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:29,047
{\an8}Hospitalized? Hyeokchan?

14
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,924
He hurt his hand badly in the lab.

15
00:01:31,007 --> 00:01:32,383
He even got surgery.

16
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:36,096
How does he know Hyeokchan?

17
00:01:38,306 --> 00:01:39,974
OUTSIDE THE LAB

18
00:01:40,517 --> 00:01:42,060
"Lab"?

19
00:01:42,685 --> 00:01:43,853
[Chan] <i>NaClO.</i>

20
00:01:43,937 --> 00:01:45,271
Sodium hypochlorite…

21
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:46,940
[officer] I guess
you majored in that field.

22
00:01:47,023 --> 00:01:49,275
It seems like you majored
in engineering, not art.

23
00:01:52,987 --> 00:01:54,197
Huh?

24
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,448
This is…

25
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:59,536
[Sujin] <i>I'm only visiting, so I'm not</i>
<i>authorized to treat patients directly.</i>

26
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:00,745
I came from Boston.

27
00:02:02,539 --> 00:02:03,540
[stutters] Boston?

28
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,084
[sighs]

29
00:02:09,337 --> 00:02:11,047
[Seok] <i>There was</i>
<i>an international conference.</i>

30
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,465
Your school…

31
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:16,678
- No, your former school…
- [Chan] That's enough.

32
00:02:22,100 --> 00:02:23,601
Boston Institute of Technology.

33
00:02:31,067 --> 00:02:33,278
[♪ soft emotional music playing]

34
00:02:35,071 --> 00:02:36,072
[Genius huffs]

35
00:02:36,739 --> 00:02:37,740
Ah.

36
00:02:39,492 --> 00:02:40,535
[sighs]

37
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:42,662
Is she upstairs?

38
00:02:45,039 --> 00:02:46,624
THANKS FOR THE

39
00:02:48,501 --> 00:02:51,129
- [line connects, ringing]
- [inhales sharply]

40
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,261
[♪ music fades]

41
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:07,812
[♪ tense music playing]

42
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,694
KANG HYEOKCHAN, GLASS TUBE, BLOOD

43
00:03:14,777 --> 00:03:17,238
KANG HYEOKCHAN HOSPITALIZED, WOMAN
THAT SOUND WAS HER BRACELET

44
00:03:27,415 --> 00:03:29,334
[exhales shakily] No…

45
00:03:39,219 --> 00:03:40,637
[Hyeokchan]
<i>Let me tell you something cool.</i>

46
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:43,348
<i>My dorm roommate is Korean,
and his name's Chan, too.</i>

47
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:45,516
[Hayeong] <i>You used to call him Chan.</i>

48
00:03:45,600 --> 00:03:47,560
<i>Your old boyfriend, Hyeokchan.</i>

49
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:49,395
Hyeokchan's roommate

50
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:53,608
was Seonu Chan?

51
00:03:53,691 --> 00:03:54,901
[vibrating]

52
00:03:54,984 --> 00:03:56,486
SEONU CHAN

53
00:03:57,862 --> 00:03:58,863
[Chan] <i>Watch out!</i>

54
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:00,073
Song Haran!

55
00:04:01,074 --> 00:04:03,117
[Haran] I met you for the first time
a few days ago.

56
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:05,078
How long have you known me?

57
00:04:05,578 --> 00:04:07,956
Tell me how you know me.

58
00:04:08,039 --> 00:04:09,582
What are you hiding?

59
00:04:12,293 --> 00:04:13,503
He's known me

60
00:04:14,879 --> 00:04:16,089
for seven years.

61
00:04:19,175 --> 00:04:20,301
[door closes]

62
00:04:25,932 --> 00:04:26,933
[♪ music fades]

63
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,272
[♪ somber music playing]

64
00:04:39,654 --> 00:04:41,239
[Haran] <i>He knew my face</i>

65
00:04:42,198 --> 00:04:44,075
and my name.

66
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,411
It's nice to meet you.

67
00:04:46,494 --> 00:04:47,495
Ah…

68
00:04:48,329 --> 00:04:49,497
It's nice to meet you.

69
00:04:50,164 --> 00:04:53,459
I saw you up close earlier,
looking at the Sisley painting.

70
00:04:55,086 --> 00:04:56,254
No…

71
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:58,506
This can't be right. No.

72
00:04:59,215 --> 00:05:00,216
No…

73
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,801
<i>Hey, it smells like rain.</i>

74
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:04,137
[Chan] <i>That's the smell</i>
<i>of organic matter diffusing.</i>

75
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,471
Petrichor.

76
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:08,266
[Haran] <i>There's another guy</i>
<i>who speaks like him.</i>

77
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,601
She doesn't like eggplants.

78
00:05:10,685 --> 00:05:12,478
[Haran] How do you know
I don't like eggplants?

79
00:05:12,562 --> 00:05:14,272
<i>Yuck. The taste of neon alien.</i>

80
00:05:14,355 --> 00:05:15,606
I'll eat those for you.

81
00:05:16,149 --> 00:05:17,233
The neon aliens.

82
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:19,944
Then…

83
00:05:21,279 --> 00:05:22,530
all those messages…

84
00:05:23,948 --> 00:05:25,616
were him pretending to be Hyeokchan?

85
00:05:31,831 --> 00:05:33,124
[exhales shakily]

86
00:05:33,207 --> 00:05:34,208
No…

87
00:05:35,251 --> 00:05:37,128
That can't be. No.

88
00:05:37,211 --> 00:05:38,338
He'll explain everything.

89
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:39,630
No…

90
00:05:39,714 --> 00:05:40,965
This doesn't make sense.

91
00:05:41,049 --> 00:05:42,467
[♪ music continues]

92
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,274
- [cell phone vibrates]
- [Chan] <i>Let's meet.</i>

93
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,525
<i>Let's meet up and talk.</i>

94
00:05:59,609 --> 00:06:00,985
<i>I'll explain everything.</i>

95
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:06,824
No, please…

96
00:06:07,325 --> 00:06:08,326
Please.

97
00:06:08,910 --> 00:06:09,911
Please…

98
00:06:21,047 --> 00:06:23,674
It must have gotten mixed up
in my stuff back then.

99
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,469
<i>Just consider this pen</i>

100
00:06:26,552 --> 00:06:27,595
<i>a pen that I found for you.</i>

101
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:32,767
I think you owe me an explanation.

102
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,477
I bought the same pen…

103
00:06:37,355 --> 00:06:38,815
when I was in the States.

104
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:41,025
Then this pen…

105
00:06:42,568 --> 00:06:44,320
He knew everything…

106
00:06:47,407 --> 00:06:48,741
[breath trembling]

107
00:06:58,418 --> 00:06:59,836
[sighs]

108
00:07:01,963 --> 00:07:02,964
[♪ music fades]

109
00:07:13,141 --> 00:07:14,642
- Hey…
- [Haran] Don't come any closer.

110
00:07:23,776 --> 00:07:25,361
Boston Institute of Technology.

111
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:27,572
Kang Hyeokchan's roommate.

112
00:07:28,614 --> 00:07:29,907
Have you really known me

113
00:07:31,075 --> 00:07:32,452
for seven years?

114
00:07:36,372 --> 00:07:37,790
[breathes shakily]

115
00:07:38,958 --> 00:07:40,626
- Song Haran.
- Don't say my name.

116
00:07:41,127 --> 00:07:42,170
[breath trembling]

117
00:07:42,253 --> 00:07:43,337
Did you have fun

118
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:45,798
pretending to be Kang Hyeokchan?

119
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:47,091
[breath trembling]

120
00:07:52,305 --> 00:07:53,681
Seonu Chan,

121
00:07:54,682 --> 00:07:55,766
who are you?

122
00:07:56,476 --> 00:07:58,478
[high-pitched ringing]

123
00:08:01,647 --> 00:08:03,107
The Seonu Chan

124
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:05,902
I liked and trusted
until just a few hours ago…

125
00:08:05,985 --> 00:08:07,487
Who is he, really?

126
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:11,491
[yells] Who are you?

127
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,075
[♪ emotional music playing]

128
00:08:13,159 --> 00:08:14,577
[stutters]

129
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:16,329
I'm sorry.

130
00:08:16,871 --> 00:08:19,207
I shouldn't have let you
find out like this.

131
00:08:19,749 --> 00:08:21,042
I should've told you…

132
00:08:21,125 --> 00:08:23,794
No wonder you were so flustered
in front of the doctor.

133
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:26,214
You didn't want to get caught,

134
00:08:27,340 --> 00:08:29,759
because she knew you were in Boston.

135
00:08:30,676 --> 00:08:32,178
Because I couldn't find out.

136
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,889
- I'll explain everything.
- Tell me.

137
00:08:36,182 --> 00:08:37,350
Did you message me

138
00:08:38,059 --> 00:08:40,144
seven years ago,
pretending to be Hyeokchan?

139
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,979
Is that true?

140
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:46,984
Answer me.

141
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:52,782
Did you really deceive me
and pretend to be Hyeokchan

142
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,117
behind his back?

143
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:00,748
I'm sorry.

144
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:03,417
[breath trembling]

145
00:09:04,418 --> 00:09:05,419
Why?

146
00:09:07,421 --> 00:09:08,464
Why did you do that?

147
00:09:11,509 --> 00:09:12,510
Our laptops

148
00:09:13,594 --> 00:09:15,763
got switched once.

149
00:09:15,846 --> 00:09:16,931
[sighs in disbelief]

150
00:09:18,599 --> 00:09:19,684
[exhales shakily]

151
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:23,062
Did you have fun
chatting with me like that?

152
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,941
Did you build some kind of fantasy
and start liking me?

153
00:09:27,024 --> 00:09:29,402
I can't even tell
which was really Hyeokchan or you…

154
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:39,370
The pen.

155
00:09:41,998 --> 00:09:42,999
The engraving.

156
00:09:45,209 --> 00:09:46,210
Who was it?

157
00:09:46,711 --> 00:09:48,379
Was it you or Hyeokchan?

158
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,219
- I'm sorry.
- [exhales shakily]

159
00:09:57,305 --> 00:09:58,306
If that's fake…

160
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:01,559
[sobbing] Even if this pen is fake…

161
00:10:02,435 --> 00:10:04,979
Then what was I holding onto
the past seven years?

162
00:10:06,105 --> 00:10:08,733
I even hurt my grandma
because of all that.

163
00:10:08,816 --> 00:10:09,817
Why…

164
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,529
You should've at least told me

165
00:10:14,572 --> 00:10:16,782
when you gave me this pen.

166
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:21,329
When I believed you like a fool,
you should've told me the truth.

167
00:10:21,412 --> 00:10:22,622
I needed time.

168
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:24,582
My memories aren't…

169
00:10:27,418 --> 00:10:28,502
[sighs exasperatedly]

170
00:10:29,295 --> 00:10:30,296
I'm sorry.

171
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:32,465
It's all my fault.

172
00:10:32,548 --> 00:10:35,217
Do you even know what it meant
for me to hold your hand?

173
00:10:35,301 --> 00:10:37,345
To open my heart to you?

174
00:10:37,428 --> 00:10:39,513
[sighs] How could you, of all people…

175
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:41,641
How could you, Seonu Chan?

176
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:43,517
[sighs dejectedly]

177
00:10:44,769 --> 00:10:47,688
I'm really sorry I hurt you
by making you find out like this.

178
00:10:49,106 --> 00:10:51,192
I won't ask you
to believe everything I say,

179
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:52,360
so please…

180
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:56,280
I was surprised that there was someone
who believed in me this much.

181
00:10:57,531 --> 00:10:58,532
I was grateful.

182
00:10:59,909 --> 00:11:01,827
But you knew me all along.

183
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:04,372
You knew what hurt me the most

184
00:11:04,872 --> 00:11:06,874
and what would break me the easiest.

185
00:11:08,209 --> 00:11:09,293
I thought…

186
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:14,590
you were like a miracle to me.

187
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,302
But to you…

188
00:11:20,262 --> 00:11:22,098
I was just an experiment.

189
00:11:24,642 --> 00:11:25,893
[Chan sighs dejectedly]

190
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,145
It's not…

191
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:31,107
No…

192
00:11:33,609 --> 00:11:34,610
[♪ music fades]

193
00:11:34,694 --> 00:11:36,153
Haran, that's not true.

194
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:37,488
Never.

195
00:11:37,988 --> 00:11:40,616
If you were fake,
you shouldn't have made me like you.

196
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:43,577
You shouldn't have made me
trust you this much!

197
00:11:46,872 --> 00:11:48,791
I didn't even know it was all fake,

198
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:50,626
and I foolishly laughed, cried,

199
00:11:50,710 --> 00:11:53,337
and was happy because of you.

200
00:11:53,421 --> 00:11:55,423
[Haran sobbing]

201
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:59,343
It must have been so fun watching me.

202
00:12:00,177 --> 00:12:01,554
Like a spring picnic.

203
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:13,107
[Chan pants]

204
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,109
Wait.

205
00:12:16,485 --> 00:12:17,653
Please.

206
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:20,990
[panting] Please, let me explain.

207
00:12:21,073 --> 00:12:22,074
Explain what?

208
00:12:23,159 --> 00:12:25,286
That you were still sincere?
That's so obvious.

209
00:12:26,662 --> 00:12:29,623
No matter what you say about it,
the truth won't change.

210
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:31,500
Everything was fake from the start,

211
00:12:32,334 --> 00:12:34,545
and every moment you spent with me,

212
00:12:35,337 --> 00:12:37,256
you were hiding that secret from me.

213
00:12:38,716 --> 00:12:40,134
[♪ melancholy music playing]

214
00:12:40,217 --> 00:12:41,635
I knew it was too good to be true.

215
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:44,430
There's no way
someone like me could be that happy.

216
00:12:45,097 --> 00:12:48,809
Whenever I feel like I'm really happy,

217
00:12:48,893 --> 00:12:49,977
I lose someone.

218
00:12:51,854 --> 00:12:52,855
[young Hadam] Hi!

219
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,815
- [Hyewon] Hi.
- [Junho] They look so excited.

220
00:12:55,357 --> 00:12:56,358
[tires screech]

221
00:12:56,442 --> 00:12:57,818
Dad!

222
00:12:57,902 --> 00:12:59,153
[Haran] <i>Mom and Dad, 13 years ago…</i>

223
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,613
[gasps, sighs]

224
00:13:00,696 --> 00:13:01,947
Just five minutes left.

225
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:04,492
- [people clamoring]
- [siren blaring]

226
00:13:05,326 --> 00:13:06,619
[Haran] <i>Hyeokchan, seven years ago…</i>

227
00:13:07,286 --> 00:13:08,412
And today.

228
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,831
You, Seonu Chan.

229
00:13:14,168 --> 00:13:16,378
This is the kind of ending that suits me.

230
00:13:17,004 --> 00:13:19,006
I'm not allowed to be happy.

231
00:13:20,424 --> 00:13:22,426
You've proven that once again.

232
00:13:23,135 --> 00:13:25,221
[breath trembling]

233
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:26,305
Haran, please.

234
00:13:27,056 --> 00:13:28,432
If we end things like this,

235
00:13:29,016 --> 00:13:32,436
you'll go back
to putting up walls around you.

236
00:13:33,229 --> 00:13:35,356
- If you do that because of me--
- You're right.

237
00:13:36,398 --> 00:13:38,651
You just pushed me back into winter again.

238
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:41,570
My past seven years, the present,

239
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,864
and the future.

240
00:13:43,948 --> 00:13:44,949
[♪ music fades]

241
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:46,700
You've ruined it all for me.

242
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:52,164
[sighs] Just let me go.

243
00:13:53,499 --> 00:13:54,625
You disgust me.

244
00:14:05,135 --> 00:14:07,137
[♪ mellow song playing]

245
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:20,067
[breathing heavily]

246
00:14:37,459 --> 00:14:38,794
[sharp inhale, groans]

247
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:43,424
[sobbing]

248
00:14:52,016 --> 00:14:53,726
[sobbing]

249
00:15:00,524 --> 00:15:02,526
[Haran] <i>Is it still valid?</i>

250
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:04,486
Being friends. The three-month trial.

251
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:07,156
Then let's do this.
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

252
00:15:07,239 --> 00:15:08,240
Let's have fun.

253
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:09,825
<i>Ms. Song!</i>

254
00:15:18,292 --> 00:15:20,669
You're Designer Song Haran, right?

255
00:15:21,503 --> 00:15:22,504
[Haran chuckles]

256
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:28,344
[Chan] <i>I'll wear this every day.</i>

257
00:15:28,427 --> 00:15:30,179
[Haran shudders]

258
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:31,972
[Haran chuckles]

259
00:15:33,098 --> 00:15:34,850
[Chan] <i>I feel like I'm in a dream.</i>

260
00:15:36,644 --> 00:15:37,811
[chuckles softly]

261
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:40,981
[♪ song continues]

262
00:15:41,065 --> 00:15:43,734
[inaudible]

263
00:15:52,868 --> 00:15:54,745
[wind whooshes]

264
00:15:54,828 --> 00:15:57,790
- [leaves rustling]
- [birds chirping]

265
00:15:57,873 --> 00:15:59,792
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

266
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:01,794
- [♪ song fades]
- [pens clatter]

267
00:16:04,046 --> 00:16:05,422
[objects clattering]

268
00:16:10,469 --> 00:16:11,470
SEONU CHAN

269
00:16:27,069 --> 00:16:28,153
[sighs]

270
00:16:31,615 --> 00:16:32,616
[sighs]

271
00:16:36,495 --> 00:16:38,497
[♪ soft emotional music playing]

272
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:01,770
[Haran] <i>I'm not allowed to be happy.</i>

273
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:04,648
You've proven that once again.

274
00:17:05,441 --> 00:17:07,651
<i>You just pushed me back into winter again.</i>

275
00:17:07,735 --> 00:17:10,529
<i>My past seven years, the present,</i>

276
00:17:10,612 --> 00:17:11,822
<i>and the future.</i>

277
00:17:11,905 --> 00:17:13,741
<i>You've ruined it all for me.</i>

278
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,493
It's my fault…

279
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,874
I have to do something.

280
00:17:24,334 --> 00:17:25,335
[exclaims softly]

281
00:17:26,378 --> 00:17:29,089
Talk it out with Haran.

282
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:33,719
If you're sincere,
I'm sure she'll understand.

283
00:17:33,802 --> 00:17:35,220
[♪ music continues]

284
00:17:50,486 --> 00:17:51,487
[sighs]

285
00:17:58,952 --> 00:17:59,953
[♪ music fades]

286
00:18:00,037 --> 00:18:01,538
- [knocks on door]
- [Hayeong] Haran?

287
00:18:02,998 --> 00:18:04,541
What's going on?

288
00:18:04,625 --> 00:18:06,502
Why are you cooped up in here again?

289
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:08,921
How is this scarf? Should I wear it?

290
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:12,674
I'm heading to work in 10 minutes.
Do you want to…

291
00:18:15,844 --> 00:18:16,845
What?

292
00:18:17,805 --> 00:18:19,098
You're sweating.

293
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:23,143
Haran, you're burning up.

294
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:26,188
I told you to dress warmly, didn't I?

295
00:18:26,271 --> 00:18:28,774
- Let's go to the hospital.
- I can just take medicine.

296
00:18:28,857 --> 00:18:30,692
Medicine won't be enough right now.

297
00:18:31,443 --> 00:18:33,028
You should just rest today…

298
00:18:33,112 --> 00:18:35,572
How can I when Grandma's away?

299
00:18:36,156 --> 00:18:38,367
I'll get dressed, so get the car ready.

300
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:39,701
[Hayeong sighs softly]

301
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:48,085
Oh… Let's talk.

302
00:18:48,710 --> 00:18:51,338
[pants] I know you don't want to see me…

303
00:18:51,421 --> 00:18:53,382
[stutters] but just hear me out.

304
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:57,052
If we end things like this,
you'll go back to how you used to be.

305
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:01,390
All right.

306
00:19:02,224 --> 00:19:04,518
You don't have to look at me
or listen to me.

307
00:19:04,601 --> 00:19:07,104
So please, just look at this.

308
00:19:11,191 --> 00:19:13,819
- [Chan stutters]
- How many pills should you take?

309
00:19:13,902 --> 00:19:16,780
- Oh? It's Chan.
- Don't open the window. Just go.

310
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:19,199
- But it's Chan.
- Just go.

311
00:19:19,908 --> 00:19:20,951
Okay.

312
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:28,333
If he came all the way here,
it must be pretty important.

313
00:19:29,126 --> 00:19:31,044
What's going on? Did you have a fight?

314
00:19:32,004 --> 00:19:33,380
Let's just go quietly.

315
00:19:34,381 --> 00:19:37,176
He looks so down, though.

316
00:19:39,219 --> 00:19:40,429
[Hayeong sighs]

317
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:45,851
Let's continue after lunch.

318
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:48,228
- All right.
- [groans]

319
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:49,897
[Haran] Can you--

320
00:19:49,980 --> 00:19:51,231
It's Chan.

321
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,357
Hey, Chan.

322
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:01,450
Ms. Song.

323
00:20:01,533 --> 00:20:03,118
I don't have any meetings today.

324
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:04,578
Don't let anyone in.

325
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,164
[Sol] Huh? But Chan…

326
00:20:07,664 --> 00:20:09,499
[Chan] I won't make any excuses.

327
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:12,461
I know you don't want to listen,
so please…

328
00:20:12,544 --> 00:20:14,755
No exceptions.
Don't let anyone in my office.

329
00:20:25,182 --> 00:20:27,351
[♪ melancholy music playing]

330
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:30,896
[hesitates] I'll buy lunch today.

331
00:20:31,480 --> 00:20:33,106
Why don't you join us since you're here?

332
00:20:33,732 --> 00:20:35,609
No, I'm okay.

333
00:20:38,904 --> 00:20:39,905
Ah.

334
00:20:40,405 --> 00:20:43,075
Please give this to her.
Don't tell her it's from me.

335
00:20:43,158 --> 00:20:44,368
[Raemee] Okay.

336
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:47,120
He looks more sick than her, though.

337
00:20:58,048 --> 00:20:59,049
[sighs]

338
00:21:07,683 --> 00:21:08,684
[♪ music fades]

339
00:21:10,310 --> 00:21:12,104
Does this one stand out too much?

340
00:21:13,897 --> 00:21:15,983
[Seunggyu] It'll feel more like noise
than a focal point.

341
00:21:16,066 --> 00:21:17,317
What do you think?

342
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:19,027
I agree.

343
00:21:19,111 --> 00:21:20,946
Then let's stick to the flow instead.

344
00:21:21,029 --> 00:21:22,322
- All right.
- Good.

345
00:21:23,532 --> 00:21:27,869
Oh. But has anyone
seen our robot, Mr. Yeon?

346
00:21:27,953 --> 00:21:31,248
I have to ask him
about our press cut deadline. [sighs]

347
00:21:31,331 --> 00:21:35,085
I haven't seen
his perfectly groomed hair for days.

348
00:21:35,168 --> 00:21:38,088
He must be incredibly busy
taking care of things for Ms. Kim.

349
00:21:38,171 --> 00:21:41,925
Right. He'll be busy
making up for her absence.

350
00:21:42,426 --> 00:21:45,470
But when did Mr. Yeon
start working in Nana Atelier?

351
00:21:46,305 --> 00:21:47,306
Since he was 19.

352
00:21:47,931 --> 00:21:48,932
[Seunggyu, Sol, and Raemee gasp]

353
00:21:49,016 --> 00:21:51,018
- Nineteen?
- [in English] Legend.

354
00:21:51,101 --> 00:21:52,811
[Sol exclaims, whines]

355
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:56,231
[in Korean] But no matter how busy he is,
he does seem to have disappeared.

356
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:58,442
- [Seunggyu] Mmm.
- Right.

357
00:21:58,942 --> 00:22:00,027
It's like he just quit.

358
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:02,112
[Sol gasps] What if he really did?

359
00:22:02,779 --> 00:22:04,781
[♪ mellow music playing]

360
00:22:07,451 --> 00:22:10,370
[Sol] He could have,
if he's been working since he was 19.

361
00:22:12,622 --> 00:22:13,623
[♪ music fades]

362
00:22:14,249 --> 00:22:16,960
I organized the color differences
and confirmed the pigment.

363
00:22:17,044 --> 00:22:19,254
I also picked the other SS looks.

364
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:21,548
And you need to approve this.

365
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,013
How are you feeling?

366
00:22:30,974 --> 00:22:33,310
- I should ask the same thing.
- What?

367
00:22:33,393 --> 00:22:35,354
You look really unwell.

368
00:22:35,437 --> 00:22:38,690
- Oh… I just have a light cold.
- That's not all, is it?

369
00:22:39,941 --> 00:22:40,942
What is it?

370
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:45,238
Has Mr. Seonu gotten worse?

371
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:48,825
No, nothing's wrong. [chuckles awkwardly]

372
00:22:48,909 --> 00:22:52,579
Just focus on your condition
before your surgery.

373
00:22:52,662 --> 00:22:54,706
Don't worry about me or the company.

374
00:22:55,540 --> 00:22:58,168
Mr. Park, you can head home today.
I'll stay here.

375
00:22:58,251 --> 00:22:59,252
[Manjae] Mmm-mmm.

376
00:22:59,836 --> 00:23:02,589
I told you I'm in charge here.

377
00:23:02,672 --> 00:23:06,551
You should hurry home and rest.

378
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:08,970
[Nana] You might end up
getting hospitalized instead of me.

379
00:23:09,054 --> 00:23:10,680
You look like you'll collapse.

380
00:23:10,764 --> 00:23:12,057
Go home.

381
00:23:12,516 --> 00:23:14,476
Then please take care of her.

382
00:23:15,352 --> 00:23:16,770
Thank you, Mr. Park.

383
00:23:17,521 --> 00:23:18,522
[in English] My pleasure.

384
00:23:18,605 --> 00:23:19,940
[chuckles]

385
00:23:20,023 --> 00:23:21,983
- [in Korean] Bye, then.
- Bye.

386
00:23:25,404 --> 00:23:27,030
It seems like something's up.

387
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:31,868
Ms. Kim Nabong, worry about yourself

388
00:23:32,411 --> 00:23:35,038
until your surgery.

389
00:23:35,122 --> 00:23:36,123
Hmm?

390
00:23:42,379 --> 00:23:43,422
[therapist] Is this okay?

391
00:23:43,505 --> 00:23:44,589
Yes, it's okay.

392
00:23:44,673 --> 00:23:46,675
- Tell me if it hurts.
- Okay.

393
00:23:47,843 --> 00:23:49,845
[therapist]
You're checking with him again.

394
00:23:49,928 --> 00:23:52,013
Of course. I should record this every day.

395
00:23:52,097 --> 00:23:54,808
He has to pass
the medical test in February.

396
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:56,726
Then let's check your ankle now.

397
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:59,229
Try pulling with strength.

398
00:24:00,188 --> 00:24:01,731
[therapist inhales sharply]

399
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:02,983
It doesn't hurt?

400
00:24:03,066 --> 00:24:04,651
No, not at all.

401
00:24:04,734 --> 00:24:08,280
[gasps] Your range of motion
has improved a lot since last week.

402
00:24:08,363 --> 00:24:09,448
Right, Doctor?

403
00:24:09,531 --> 00:24:11,074
[therapist] Yes. [chuckles]

404
00:24:11,158 --> 00:24:13,410
Then, next week,
we'll fit you with an ankle brace

405
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:14,703
and work on standing up.

406
00:24:14,786 --> 00:24:16,913
Don't strain yourself. Good job.

407
00:24:16,997 --> 00:24:18,373
- Thank you.
- Bye.

408
00:24:19,374 --> 00:24:21,626
That was two degrees more than last week.

409
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:23,503
Are you sure it didn't hurt?

410
00:24:23,587 --> 00:24:25,714
I know my body better than anyone.

411
00:24:25,797 --> 00:24:29,342
I feel like I'll be able to get up soon
and start throwing balls.

412
00:24:29,426 --> 00:24:30,927
[chuckles]

413
00:24:31,011 --> 00:24:34,181
Mr. Cha, you really have
exceptional recovery speed,

414
00:24:34,264 --> 00:24:35,682
- as expected.
- [clears throat]

415
00:24:35,765 --> 00:24:38,727
Then let's start
outdoors practice tomorrow

416
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:40,979
so you don't lose your touch.

417
00:24:41,771 --> 00:24:44,274
Yes, Coach. Let's do this.

418
00:24:44,357 --> 00:24:45,358
[both chuckle]

419
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:46,943
- [cell phone vibrating]
- Ah.

420
00:24:48,862 --> 00:24:50,155
- Hang on.
- Sure.

421
00:24:50,238 --> 00:24:51,490
Hello?

422
00:25:07,005 --> 00:25:08,048
Come in.

423
00:25:11,051 --> 00:25:12,636
Are you just going to leave again?

424
00:25:13,178 --> 00:25:14,471
Come in.

425
00:25:17,599 --> 00:25:18,683
Mr. Yeon.

426
00:25:42,916 --> 00:25:44,084
I've failed you again.

427
00:25:46,545 --> 00:25:49,172
I've never protected you properly.

428
00:25:50,465 --> 00:25:51,758
[breath trembling]

429
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:54,594
I'm sorry.

430
00:25:54,678 --> 00:25:55,887
So,

431
00:25:58,056 --> 00:26:00,559
were you going to wait until I recovered

432
00:26:01,560 --> 00:26:02,769
and try to quit again?

433
00:26:03,562 --> 00:26:05,188
Like that day, 13 years ago?

434
00:26:05,272 --> 00:26:07,274
[♪ melancholy music playing]

435
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:13,029
Good job. You can go now.

436
00:26:14,155 --> 00:26:15,657
Ms. Kim…

437
00:26:15,740 --> 00:26:18,159
LETTER OF RESIGNATION

438
00:26:18,243 --> 00:26:19,536
I'm sorry, Ms. Kim.

439
00:26:20,203 --> 00:26:21,955
If only I hadn't been sick that day…

440
00:26:23,039 --> 00:26:24,541
If I'd been the one driving…

441
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,670
I couldn't even repay you
for your kindness.

442
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:30,171
I'm sorry.

443
00:26:31,965 --> 00:26:34,509
If you have time to talk such nonsense,

444
00:26:35,051 --> 00:26:36,052
use that time

445
00:26:37,721 --> 00:26:38,972
to prepare for college.

446
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,601
You'd better get accepted in one try.

447
00:26:43,768 --> 00:26:44,769
[♪ music fades]

448
00:26:46,229 --> 00:26:48,523
<i>You made that same face</i>

449
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:51,192
<i>after Hyewon and Junho's funeral.</i>

450
00:26:55,989 --> 00:26:57,949
When I met you for the first time,

451
00:26:59,492 --> 00:27:01,953
do you know why I told you to come see me?

452
00:27:03,622 --> 00:27:05,081
You reminded me of my past.

453
00:27:06,541 --> 00:27:08,251
Even if no one noticed,

454
00:27:09,669 --> 00:27:11,296
I did my best

455
00:27:12,547 --> 00:27:15,884
and worked so hard on my own
in Paris when I was 20.

456
00:27:18,928 --> 00:27:20,889
[♪ sentimental music playing]

457
00:27:20,972 --> 00:27:22,474
As soon as I turned 20,

458
00:27:22,557 --> 00:27:24,976
I flew to Paris alone
with no friends or family.

459
00:27:25,060 --> 00:27:28,355
I threw myself
into both studying and love.

460
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:31,191
But I suddenly got pregnant

461
00:27:31,775 --> 00:27:33,610
and gave birth by myself.

462
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:35,570
I struggled so hard

463
00:27:36,571 --> 00:27:39,282
attending fashion school,
carrying a baby on my back.

464
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:47,999
I told myself that someone
would notice my efforts someday,

465
00:27:49,417 --> 00:27:50,835
and I pushed through.

466
00:27:51,711 --> 00:27:52,796
[sobs]

467
00:27:52,879 --> 00:27:54,214
[Nana] Once I succeeded,

468
00:27:55,924 --> 00:27:57,008
I felt so much pity

469
00:27:58,593 --> 00:27:59,969
and pride

470
00:28:00,679 --> 00:28:02,263
for myself back then.

471
00:28:06,267 --> 00:28:07,602
I saw you that day,

472
00:28:08,728 --> 00:28:11,398
and I felt the same way about you.

473
00:28:12,732 --> 00:28:14,317
That's why I reached out a hand.

474
00:28:14,401 --> 00:28:17,821
Because I wanted to acknowledge
your efforts.

475
00:28:18,613 --> 00:28:19,614
You…

476
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:22,367
took care of me…

477
00:28:25,328 --> 00:28:27,205
and changed my life, but…

478
00:28:27,288 --> 00:28:29,207
I never thought of it like that,

479
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:32,669
but you've already repaid me enough.

480
00:28:32,752 --> 00:28:34,003
Without you,

481
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:36,923
neither I nor my company nor my family

482
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:39,884
would have gotten this far.

483
00:28:39,968 --> 00:28:41,052
No.

484
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:42,971
I…

485
00:28:44,556 --> 00:28:46,307
I don't have the right to stay…

486
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:47,767
Taeseok.

487
00:28:53,481 --> 00:28:54,774
Put down that burden now.

488
00:28:58,361 --> 00:29:00,363
You couldn't have prevented the accident

489
00:29:01,281 --> 00:29:02,615
by driving that day,

490
00:29:03,783 --> 00:29:05,493
nor could you have prevented this

491
00:29:06,411 --> 00:29:07,829
by noticing more quickly.

492
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:11,499
No one in my family
blames you for what happened.

493
00:29:11,583 --> 00:29:14,544
You've been holding onto that guilt
because you're too kind.

494
00:29:16,004 --> 00:29:17,547
But you don't have to do that.

495
00:29:17,630 --> 00:29:19,799
- [sobbing]
- [Nana] Put it all down now.

496
00:29:25,847 --> 00:29:27,265
You've done a great job so far

497
00:29:28,266 --> 00:29:29,976
working by my side.

498
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:34,814
So stay with me.

499
00:29:34,898 --> 00:29:37,692
[sobbing]

500
00:29:44,449 --> 00:29:46,451
[Taeseok crying]

501
00:29:54,834 --> 00:29:55,835
{\an8}[young Hayeong] Mr. Yeon.

502
00:29:57,253 --> 00:29:58,505
[young Taeseok] I'm sorry.

503
00:29:58,588 --> 00:29:59,881
I'm really sorry.

504
00:29:59,964 --> 00:30:01,299
I'm sorry.

505
00:30:01,382 --> 00:30:02,842
I'm really sorry.

506
00:30:04,219 --> 00:30:05,220
I…

507
00:30:06,304 --> 00:30:07,972
shouldn't be sick.

508
00:30:11,935 --> 00:30:13,937
[Taeseok crying]

509
00:30:20,026 --> 00:30:22,028
[footsteps approaching]

510
00:30:22,111 --> 00:30:23,112
[♪ music ends]

511
00:30:29,577 --> 00:30:32,205
Do you want one?

512
00:30:41,339 --> 00:30:42,423
[Hayeong sighs]

513
00:30:45,134 --> 00:30:46,469
I'm sorry.

514
00:30:47,470 --> 00:30:49,222
I didn't mean to eavesdrop,

515
00:30:49,305 --> 00:30:53,685
but I brought fruits for Grandma
and ended up overhearing.

516
00:30:56,104 --> 00:30:59,899
Ah. So that's why
you were at Mom and Dad's grave.

517
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,568
Okay. I understand now.

518
00:31:02,610 --> 00:31:05,196
- I'm sorry.
- Stop saying you're sorry.

519
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:09,200
Like Grandma said,
none of us have ever blamed you.

520
00:31:09,284 --> 00:31:10,660
Not for a single second.

521
00:31:10,743 --> 00:31:13,204
Mom, Dad. It's not his fault, right?

522
00:31:15,748 --> 00:31:17,959
You heard that, right? They said no.

523
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:20,879
[sighs softly]

524
00:31:24,048 --> 00:31:25,049
[Hayeong] Here.

525
00:31:25,133 --> 00:31:29,512
Have this sweet and sour candy
that you love so much…

526
00:31:34,350 --> 00:31:35,894
and leave all your burdens behind.

527
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:38,938
[chuckles softly]

528
00:31:39,606 --> 00:31:40,607
Have this

529
00:31:41,649 --> 00:31:42,901
and cheer up.

530
00:31:46,529 --> 00:31:48,448
- You're giving this to me again.
- What?

531
00:31:48,990 --> 00:31:51,200
Didn't you give me one last time?

532
00:31:52,493 --> 00:31:53,578
Did I?

533
00:31:57,373 --> 00:32:00,168
[winces] It's so sour. Why is it so sour?

534
00:32:03,421 --> 00:32:04,631
[chuckles]

535
00:32:04,714 --> 00:32:06,716
[♪ heartwarming music playing]

536
00:32:07,592 --> 00:32:10,178
YOU SAVED ME TOO

537
00:32:13,264 --> 00:32:14,265
[Haran sighs]

538
00:32:15,183 --> 00:32:16,267
[Chan stutters]

539
00:32:16,351 --> 00:32:18,853
No exceptions.
Don't let anyone in my office.

540
00:32:23,733 --> 00:32:24,734
[sighs softly]

541
00:32:25,693 --> 00:32:27,528
[coughs, sniffles]

542
00:32:29,948 --> 00:32:32,575
[cell phone vibrating]

543
00:32:33,326 --> 00:32:35,036
MR. PARK

544
00:32:39,123 --> 00:32:40,124
Yes, Mr. Park.

545
00:32:40,792 --> 00:32:42,168
What's wrong with your voice?

546
00:32:42,251 --> 00:32:43,461
Did you catch a cold?

547
00:32:43,544 --> 00:32:44,545
Oh…

548
00:32:46,464 --> 00:32:49,133
Maybe it's because you're not here.
[chuckles softly]

549
00:32:49,217 --> 00:32:50,510
I have no one to talk to,

550
00:32:51,719 --> 00:32:54,931
so I guess my voice is a bit rusty.
[clears throat]

551
00:32:55,515 --> 00:32:57,934
[inhales sharply] Is…

552
00:32:59,018 --> 00:33:00,478
something the matter?

553
00:33:01,104 --> 00:33:03,606
Besides the fact that I miss you,
everything's fine.

554
00:33:04,399 --> 00:33:06,150
It must be tough at the hospital.

555
00:33:07,610 --> 00:33:10,238
I'm doing well here with Genius,

556
00:33:11,614 --> 00:33:12,657
so don't worry

557
00:33:13,658 --> 00:33:15,076
and take care of yourself, too.

558
00:33:15,743 --> 00:33:16,828
All right.

559
00:33:18,329 --> 00:33:19,414
[cell phone beeps]

560
00:33:21,582 --> 00:33:24,752
[Genius whining]

561
00:33:28,089 --> 00:33:29,298
I'm okay.

562
00:33:30,591 --> 00:33:33,678
No, I'll make sure everything's okay.

563
00:33:36,848 --> 00:33:38,850
Everything will be okay.

564
00:33:46,774 --> 00:33:48,109
Song Haran.

565
00:33:49,444 --> 00:33:50,445
[♪ music fades]

566
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:51,946
You saved me,

567
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:53,990
seven years ago.

568
00:33:54,657 --> 00:33:56,200
You saved me back then!

569
00:34:02,373 --> 00:34:03,499
[Chan panting]

570
00:34:05,793 --> 00:34:06,794
I'm sorry.

571
00:34:07,503 --> 00:34:09,338
Seven years ago and now,

572
00:34:09,422 --> 00:34:11,758
I've wanted to show you the real me.

573
00:34:13,426 --> 00:34:15,887
I should have told you, no matter what.

574
00:34:17,388 --> 00:34:18,431
[Chan sighs]

575
00:34:21,142 --> 00:34:22,268
It's all my fault.

576
00:34:26,898 --> 00:34:29,776
Please, just look at this.
Everything's in here.

577
00:34:30,902 --> 00:34:33,738
Stories that you don't know
about back then.

578
00:34:37,825 --> 00:34:39,160
Let me ask you two things.

579
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,663
Just say yes or no.

580
00:34:46,125 --> 00:34:47,585
If I look at this,

581
00:34:49,712 --> 00:34:51,130
will it change the fact

582
00:34:53,299 --> 00:34:55,968
that you pretended to be Hyeokchan
and messaged me…

583
00:34:59,097 --> 00:35:00,098
seven years ago?

584
00:35:03,226 --> 00:35:05,394
[♪ melancholy music playing]

585
00:35:05,478 --> 00:35:07,021
- No.
- [Haran] Then,

586
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:09,565
does it change the fact

587
00:35:11,651 --> 00:35:14,320
that you kept this secret from me
the whole time…

588
00:35:17,365 --> 00:35:18,449
while you were with me?

589
00:35:19,492 --> 00:35:21,661
- Haran.
- Say yes or no.

590
00:35:24,956 --> 00:35:25,957
No.

591
00:35:27,667 --> 00:35:29,669
- But--
- Then it won't change my mind.

592
00:35:31,254 --> 00:35:32,839
If those two facts don't change,

593
00:35:32,922 --> 00:35:35,091
then whatever explanation you give

594
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:37,343
or whatever you do,

595
00:35:38,094 --> 00:35:39,470
it won't change my mind.

596
00:35:42,098 --> 00:35:46,185
If you still think the lies you told
can be explained by something,

597
00:35:47,812 --> 00:35:49,730
then you still have no clue

598
00:35:52,024 --> 00:35:53,901
how you've shattered my heart

599
00:35:55,736 --> 00:35:59,532
and how you've destroyed
the past seven years of my life.

600
00:36:01,993 --> 00:36:03,828
Don't ever show up in front of me again.

601
00:36:05,580 --> 00:36:06,789
When I see you,

602
00:36:08,332 --> 00:36:12,253
I feel like I'm going to lose my mind
thinking about the seven years I lost.

603
00:36:16,299 --> 00:36:18,134
[Chan] I won't even
think about staying with you.

604
00:36:18,217 --> 00:36:21,179
But you'll go back
to how you were seven years ago…

605
00:36:22,054 --> 00:36:23,139
[breath trembling]

606
00:36:27,476 --> 00:36:29,770
[high-pitched ringing]

607
00:36:29,854 --> 00:36:30,938
[groans]

608
00:36:32,899 --> 00:36:34,692
[groaning]

609
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:37,028
[grunts]

610
00:36:37,111 --> 00:36:39,113
[breathing heavily]

611
00:36:57,089 --> 00:36:58,507
[♪ music swells]

612
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:21,822
[♪ music fades]

613
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:24,700
- [exclaims] Cha Yougyum!
- [clears throat]

614
00:37:24,784 --> 00:37:26,661
Your pitching is still amazing.

615
00:37:26,744 --> 00:37:31,415
No wonder you were always named MVP
at every tournament.

616
00:37:31,499 --> 00:37:32,583
[Hadam chuckles]

617
00:37:34,752 --> 00:37:35,753
[inhales sharply]

618
00:37:36,754 --> 00:37:37,755
[grunts]

619
00:37:38,714 --> 00:37:40,549
Oh, gosh, I missed it.

620
00:37:42,927 --> 00:37:44,178
[sighs softly]

621
00:37:45,972 --> 00:37:47,306
Hadam, let's stop.

622
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:48,599
You must be tired.

623
00:37:48,683 --> 00:37:50,726
I'll ask Changmo to help me later.

624
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:52,687
No. We can do it.

625
00:37:52,770 --> 00:37:54,063
Let's go.

626
00:37:55,648 --> 00:37:57,316
All right, throw it.

627
00:38:02,989 --> 00:38:04,323
[grunts]

628
00:38:04,407 --> 00:38:07,368
Gosh, I missed it again. I'll go get it.

629
00:38:14,875 --> 00:38:15,876
[sighs]

630
00:38:18,045 --> 00:38:19,213
[sighs worriedly]

631
00:38:23,134 --> 00:38:24,343
Did we overdo it?

632
00:38:25,094 --> 00:38:26,095
You must be tired.

633
00:38:26,846 --> 00:38:27,888
Not at all.

634
00:38:27,972 --> 00:38:29,473
I know my body best.

635
00:38:29,557 --> 00:38:31,600
[inhales sharply] I feel much lighter now.

636
00:38:33,352 --> 00:38:34,353
Oh, right.

637
00:38:35,604 --> 00:38:39,275
My team's visiting later,
so it's going to be really noisy.

638
00:38:39,358 --> 00:38:40,568
You should head home now.

639
00:38:40,651 --> 00:38:43,362
Then I should go and study rehabilitation.

640
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:46,574
Have fun with the guys.
I'll call you later.

641
00:38:46,657 --> 00:38:47,742
Okay.

642
00:38:49,869 --> 00:38:51,495
[sighs dreamily]

643
00:38:52,079 --> 00:38:53,497
Those punks.

644
00:38:53,581 --> 00:38:56,292
I should give them some snacks.

645
00:38:57,126 --> 00:38:59,420
Hmm? It's pretty quiet, though.

646
00:39:03,007 --> 00:39:04,508
[Yougyum sobbing]

647
00:39:06,594 --> 00:39:08,554
[♪ emotional music playing]

648
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:09,972
[umpire] <i>Out!</i>

649
00:39:10,056 --> 00:39:11,390
{\an8}[players cheering]

650
00:39:11,474 --> 00:39:13,225
{\an8}FINAL, CHEONGSOL HIGH 3
HANEUL HIGH 2

651
00:39:14,518 --> 00:39:15,519
[sniffles]

652
00:39:21,233 --> 00:39:22,943
[sniffles]

653
00:39:23,861 --> 00:39:25,321
[stutters] Yougyum.

654
00:39:27,698 --> 00:39:28,699
[Yougyum] Hadam…

655
00:39:30,326 --> 00:39:31,452
What do I do?

656
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:35,915
[breathes shakily]

657
00:39:37,458 --> 00:39:38,459
I…

658
00:39:39,001 --> 00:39:40,795
I don't think I can make it.

659
00:39:42,838 --> 00:39:45,841
I know my body better than anyone.

660
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:49,220
[Yougyum crying]

661
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:05,319
CHEONGSOL HIGH SCHOOL WINS

662
00:40:11,409 --> 00:40:12,410
[♪ music fades]

663
00:40:17,456 --> 00:40:18,541
What is it?

664
00:40:19,542 --> 00:40:20,543
Can't you sleep?

665
00:40:21,001 --> 00:40:22,378
Should I turn the light off?

666
00:40:22,461 --> 00:40:23,462
No.

667
00:40:23,546 --> 00:40:24,547
Manjae,

668
00:40:25,381 --> 00:40:26,507
you should go home.

669
00:40:27,341 --> 00:40:28,717
Go and sleep comfortably.

670
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:32,096
[Manjae] I'll go once you're asleep.

671
00:40:32,638 --> 00:40:34,140
But why can't you sleep?

672
00:40:37,268 --> 00:40:38,269
I just…

673
00:40:39,645 --> 00:40:41,480
have a lot on my mind.

674
00:40:42,356 --> 00:40:43,357
Goodness.

675
00:40:43,858 --> 00:40:45,067
It's snowing.

676
00:40:46,444 --> 00:40:48,362
[Manjae] Oh. It is.

677
00:40:54,994 --> 00:40:57,746
Why do you have a lot on your mind?

678
00:40:58,581 --> 00:41:02,835
You know I've been tough
since I was little, right?

679
00:41:04,170 --> 00:41:05,171
But…

680
00:41:06,589 --> 00:41:09,633
thinking about going under anesthesia
and getting surgery

681
00:41:11,469 --> 00:41:12,761
makes me feel a bit nervous.

682
00:41:18,100 --> 00:41:20,936
I'm sure the surgery will go well.

683
00:41:21,770 --> 00:41:24,899
Just be yourself, the strong Kim Nana,

684
00:41:26,025 --> 00:41:27,151
and get through this.

685
00:41:27,902 --> 00:41:32,072
I'm more worried about something else
than drilling a hole in my skull.

686
00:41:32,823 --> 00:41:33,824
What is it?

687
00:41:35,201 --> 00:41:36,952
I have to shave my head here.

688
00:41:37,786 --> 00:41:39,997
That would ruin my look.

689
00:41:40,498 --> 00:41:42,082
Why does that worry me more?

690
00:41:42,208 --> 00:41:44,502
[laughs]

691
00:41:44,585 --> 00:41:47,213
You really are the Chuncheon fashionista.

692
00:41:47,296 --> 00:41:48,547
[laughs]

693
00:41:50,549 --> 00:41:51,550
This won't do.

694
00:41:52,259 --> 00:41:55,387
I should protect your look.

695
00:41:56,263 --> 00:41:57,515
Hang on.

696
00:41:57,598 --> 00:41:58,724
What?

697
00:42:01,435 --> 00:42:02,436
Oh, my.

698
00:42:03,562 --> 00:42:05,439
This is hand-knitted.

699
00:42:06,482 --> 00:42:07,858
Did you really…

700
00:42:09,318 --> 00:42:11,320
[♪ lighthearted music playing]

701
00:42:13,405 --> 00:42:17,159
[Manjae] <i>I knitted it in secret</i>
<i>while you were sleeping.</i>

702
00:42:18,827 --> 00:42:22,206
<i>But I think I'm a knitting genius.</i>

703
00:42:23,290 --> 00:42:25,626
- I followed along easily.
- [gasps]

704
00:42:25,709 --> 00:42:27,086
I might have to open

705
00:42:27,711 --> 00:42:30,464
a knitting workshop in my coffee shop.

706
00:42:30,548 --> 00:42:31,715
- Huh?
- [chuckles]

707
00:42:31,799 --> 00:42:33,175
How did you…

708
00:42:33,259 --> 00:42:36,220
Would you like to try it on?

709
00:42:41,725 --> 00:42:42,726
Wow.

710
00:42:44,937 --> 00:42:46,146
You look beautiful.

711
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:47,356
- Really?
- Yes.

712
00:42:47,439 --> 00:42:48,566
- Let me see.
- Okay.

713
00:42:50,776 --> 00:42:51,944
Here, look.

714
00:42:52,653 --> 00:42:54,196
[gasps, giggles]

715
00:42:57,491 --> 00:42:59,076
- [chuckles]
- Nabong.

716
00:42:59,827 --> 00:43:01,579
After the surgery,

717
00:43:04,081 --> 00:43:05,249
why don't you rest

718
00:43:06,458 --> 00:43:07,459
by my side?

719
00:43:08,836 --> 00:43:09,837
What?

720
00:43:09,920 --> 00:43:11,213
[Manjae] Kim Nabong.

721
00:43:12,339 --> 00:43:15,009
It took a long time,

722
00:43:16,135 --> 00:43:17,636
but will you begin

723
00:43:18,304 --> 00:43:20,764
your second "La Vie en Rose"

724
00:43:21,599 --> 00:43:23,642
with me, Park Manjae?

725
00:43:31,191 --> 00:43:32,401
Hmm?

726
00:43:33,444 --> 00:43:34,445
Manjae.

727
00:43:58,093 --> 00:44:00,763
You've been through so much all this time.

728
00:44:02,640 --> 00:44:04,016
So get some rest

729
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:06,477
by my side now.

730
00:44:18,322 --> 00:44:19,323
[♪ music ends]

731
00:44:20,908 --> 00:44:22,034
Hey, roomie.

732
00:44:22,993 --> 00:44:24,912
Why are you sitting there in the dark?

733
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:33,170
Hey.

734
00:44:33,837 --> 00:44:35,005
Is something wrong?

735
00:44:37,007 --> 00:44:38,050
She…

736
00:44:39,343 --> 00:44:40,886
found out about everything.

737
00:44:41,720 --> 00:44:43,555
I didn't have the chance to explain.

738
00:44:49,770 --> 00:44:51,397
It's all my fault,

739
00:44:52,439 --> 00:44:55,901
but she's the one suffering
when she did nothing wrong.

740
00:44:57,069 --> 00:44:58,946
It hurts so much

741
00:45:02,074 --> 00:45:03,659
to see her in pain…

742
00:45:05,452 --> 00:45:07,996
[scoffs] But I must be crazy.

743
00:45:09,998 --> 00:45:11,417
Despite everything,

744
00:45:14,920 --> 00:45:15,921
I still

745
00:45:17,631 --> 00:45:19,508
want to see her so badly.

746
00:45:21,301 --> 00:45:22,803
[Manjae sighs]

747
00:45:24,388 --> 00:45:26,223
If I lose her like this,

748
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:29,893
if I…

749
00:45:31,895 --> 00:45:33,856
make her return to her old self,

750
00:45:35,107 --> 00:45:36,108
then…

751
00:45:37,234 --> 00:45:38,819
[sighs dejectedly] Then…

752
00:45:40,529 --> 00:45:42,072
Oh, dear…

753
00:45:43,615 --> 00:45:47,411
I did wonder if something was wrong. Gosh.

754
00:45:47,494 --> 00:45:48,579
[mumbles]

755
00:45:49,872 --> 00:45:50,873
[exclaims softly]

756
00:45:50,956 --> 00:45:51,957
You're burning up.

757
00:45:52,040 --> 00:45:53,584
How long have you been like this?

758
00:45:54,084 --> 00:45:56,086
- Huh? Oh?
- [Chan sighs]

759
00:45:56,170 --> 00:45:58,797
[exclaims worriedly] Hey! Roomie!

760
00:45:58,881 --> 00:45:59,923
Hey!

761
00:46:00,007 --> 00:46:01,091
Chan!

762
00:46:04,261 --> 00:46:05,679
Goodness.

763
00:46:12,269 --> 00:46:15,856
[Chan] <i>I want to stay by her side</i>

764
00:46:16,690 --> 00:46:19,026
in spring, in summer,

765
00:46:19,109 --> 00:46:20,736
in fall, and in winter.

766
00:46:21,487 --> 00:46:22,488
I want

767
00:46:22,571 --> 00:46:24,948
to stay by her side,

768
00:46:25,032 --> 00:46:26,909
but I don't know what to do.

769
00:46:26,992 --> 00:46:28,285
[♪ soft emotional music playing]

770
00:46:28,368 --> 00:46:31,288
Do you need someone to talk to?

771
00:46:32,247 --> 00:46:33,582
Ah…

772
00:46:33,665 --> 00:46:35,334
I made some assumptions,

773
00:46:36,001 --> 00:46:39,171
but there was a lot more I didn't know.

774
00:46:40,506 --> 00:46:43,300
You must have had
such a hard time until now.

775
00:46:44,134 --> 00:46:45,552
You've been through a lot.

776
00:46:46,553 --> 00:46:49,348
I want to tell her everything
and stay by her side,

777
00:46:50,057 --> 00:46:51,850
but if I tell her about myself,

778
00:46:54,269 --> 00:46:55,521
it will hurt her.

779
00:46:56,730 --> 00:46:58,607
I'm not even sure

780
00:46:58,690 --> 00:47:01,276
if I can explain myself to her
without reopening

781
00:47:01,860 --> 00:47:02,903
[sighs]

782
00:47:03,529 --> 00:47:04,655
her old wounds.

783
00:47:05,489 --> 00:47:07,282
But if you're this sincere,

784
00:47:07,866 --> 00:47:10,869
don't you think
she'll realize it in the end?

785
00:47:11,829 --> 00:47:14,289
To be honest, I'm scared.

786
00:47:15,624 --> 00:47:17,543
If I act rashly,

787
00:47:17,626 --> 00:47:20,671
my flawed memories might ruin everything.

788
00:47:21,255 --> 00:47:22,256
I'm scared…

789
00:47:25,676 --> 00:47:27,219
I'll hurt her again.

790
00:47:27,761 --> 00:47:28,804
Chan.

791
00:47:30,097 --> 00:47:31,807
After living all these years,

792
00:47:32,266 --> 00:47:35,143
what I've learned is that
waiting until everything's perfect

793
00:47:35,227 --> 00:47:37,020
isn't always the answer.

794
00:47:37,771 --> 00:47:40,190
For people and for love.

795
00:47:41,024 --> 00:47:42,276
[in Latin] <i>"Memento Mori."</i>

796
00:47:42,776 --> 00:47:44,319
[in Korean] You said
you don't want regrets.

797
00:47:44,903 --> 00:47:46,029
If you keep waiting,

798
00:47:46,113 --> 00:47:48,198
you might lose your chance
and regret it later.

799
00:47:48,282 --> 00:47:51,618
Why don't you show her
how sincere you are first?

800
00:47:52,536 --> 00:47:55,581
It won't be too late
to take care of other things later.

801
00:47:57,332 --> 00:47:58,750
[♪ music continues]

802
00:48:04,172 --> 00:48:07,926
[Chan] <i>I should get ready</i>
<i>to explain myself to her.</i>

803
00:48:10,345 --> 00:48:11,555
<i>I should start</i>

804
00:48:12,139 --> 00:48:14,057
<i>by what happened seven years ago</i>

805
00:48:16,768 --> 00:48:18,353
<i>and tell her in my own way.</i>

806
00:48:22,608 --> 00:48:23,609
[♪ music fades]

807
00:48:23,692 --> 00:48:25,444
[shudders] It's so cold.

808
00:48:25,527 --> 00:48:28,614
Why are you brooding out here in the cold?

809
00:48:28,697 --> 00:48:30,157
What time is it?

810
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:31,575
[Hayeong] It's past midnight.

811
00:48:31,658 --> 00:48:33,952
How long have you been here?
You're already unwell.

812
00:48:34,036 --> 00:48:35,037
Come inside.

813
00:48:35,996 --> 00:48:38,206
Oh, uh… Did you go to the hospital?

814
00:48:40,208 --> 00:48:42,169
Haran, what is it?

815
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:44,838
Huh? Is something wrong?

816
00:48:45,505 --> 00:48:46,798
What's going on?

817
00:48:47,382 --> 00:48:49,134
- Hayeong.
- Yes?

818
00:48:50,636 --> 00:48:51,970
I want to wake up.

819
00:48:54,723 --> 00:48:57,267
I thought I was in a dream until now,

820
00:48:58,644 --> 00:49:00,228
but I guess it was a nightmare.

821
00:49:01,605 --> 00:49:02,940
[♪ somber music playing]

822
00:49:03,023 --> 00:49:04,900
I want to wake up,

823
00:49:06,109 --> 00:49:07,819
but I don't know how.

824
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:13,283
- Haran.
- We're not meant to be together.

825
00:49:15,619 --> 00:49:18,997
I have to forget things
that seem impossible to forget.

826
00:49:22,084 --> 00:49:23,460
But I don't know

827
00:49:25,087 --> 00:49:27,172
how to get over everything.

828
00:49:29,591 --> 00:49:30,592
[Hayeong sighs softly]

829
00:49:34,221 --> 00:49:35,514
[sighs]

830
00:49:41,228 --> 00:49:43,146
- [ice cubes clacking]
- [Hayeong sighs]

831
00:49:44,356 --> 00:49:45,565
[Hayeong grunts softly]

832
00:49:49,152 --> 00:49:50,153
[thermometer beeps]

833
00:49:51,697 --> 00:49:54,282
[sighs in relief] Her fever dropped.

834
00:49:56,702 --> 00:49:58,203
Gosh…

835
00:50:03,625 --> 00:50:04,626
[grunts softly]

836
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:07,004
[♪ music fades]

837
00:50:07,087 --> 00:50:08,130
What?

838
00:50:09,673 --> 00:50:11,717
Gosh. What time is it?

839
00:50:11,800 --> 00:50:13,927
0202
NOV 29 SAT

840
00:50:14,636 --> 00:50:15,762
Are you here?

841
00:50:16,888 --> 00:50:17,889
What?

842
00:50:19,099 --> 00:50:20,267
Where did she go?

843
00:50:21,893 --> 00:50:22,936
Haran!

844
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,940
- [sighs wearily]
- [line connects, ringing]

845
00:50:27,024 --> 00:50:29,109
[cell phone vibrating]

846
00:50:30,444 --> 00:50:32,279
HAYEONG

847
00:50:34,031 --> 00:50:35,824
[panting] What?

848
00:50:37,868 --> 00:50:39,411
Where did she go?

849
00:50:45,751 --> 00:50:46,752
[cell phone vibrating]

850
00:50:46,835 --> 00:50:48,086
DESIGNER SONG HAYEONG

851
00:50:48,670 --> 00:50:50,672
[breathing heavily]

852
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:52,174
[grunts]

853
00:50:52,799 --> 00:50:54,801
[cell phone continues vibrating]

854
00:50:56,928 --> 00:50:58,263
[groans softly]

855
00:50:58,972 --> 00:51:00,098
[sighing]

856
00:51:07,064 --> 00:51:08,940
[groans softly] Hey, Hayeong.

857
00:51:09,024 --> 00:51:11,902
Chan, sorry to call you so late.

858
00:51:12,611 --> 00:51:14,321
But did Haran contact you?

859
00:51:16,073 --> 00:51:18,867
[grunts] Why? What's wrong?

860
00:51:18,950 --> 00:51:21,203
Haran's gone.

861
00:51:21,286 --> 00:51:24,164
The car's gone,
but she's not at the office either.

862
00:51:24,247 --> 00:51:28,085
You're the only one
I could ask where she could be.

863
00:51:29,211 --> 00:51:31,963
<i>I feel so anxious after what she said.</i>

864
00:51:32,047 --> 00:51:36,176
<i>She said she was in a dream,
but it was a nightmare.</i>

865
00:51:36,885 --> 00:51:37,886
[breath trembling]

866
00:51:39,554 --> 00:51:41,014
[♪ tense music playing]

867
00:51:41,098 --> 00:51:43,225
- I think I know where she is.
- [Manjae exclaims worriedly]

868
00:51:43,308 --> 00:51:45,268
Where are you going?
You're still burning up.

869
00:51:45,352 --> 00:51:47,187
I have to go find her.

870
00:51:48,063 --> 00:51:49,064
It has to be me.

871
00:51:49,147 --> 00:51:52,067
[stutters] What are you saying?
Did something happen to Haran?

872
00:51:53,151 --> 00:51:54,736
Huh? Chan!

873
00:51:55,195 --> 00:51:56,613
[♪ music continues]

874
00:52:01,034 --> 00:52:02,994
[Hayeong] <i>She said</i>
<i>you're not meant to be together</i>

875
00:52:03,703 --> 00:52:05,330
<i>and that she has to forget it.</i>

876
00:52:05,413 --> 00:52:08,208
<i>I couldn't understand what she was saying,</i>

877
00:52:08,792 --> 00:52:10,961
<i>but she's really sick right now.</i>

878
00:52:12,087 --> 00:52:13,713
[Chan] <i>I feel like I'm in a dream.</i>

879
00:52:13,797 --> 00:52:16,842
[Haran] <i>Those words sounded a bit sad.</i>

880
00:52:17,384 --> 00:52:20,512
<i>It sounds like
they're not meant to be together.</i>

881
00:52:21,138 --> 00:52:23,348
- [engine revving]
- [navigator beeping]

882
00:52:23,431 --> 00:52:25,433
[breathing shakily]

883
00:52:36,695 --> 00:52:40,115
[Haran] I said I won't ever forget

884
00:52:40,198 --> 00:52:42,242
this moment.

885
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:44,911
Ah, and in spring…

886
00:52:44,995 --> 00:52:47,622
[Chan] <i>Let's go see</i>
<i>the cherry blossoms in spring.</i>

887
00:52:47,706 --> 00:52:49,833
We'll have shaved ice in summer…

888
00:52:50,584 --> 00:52:52,878
Oh, and go to the beach.

889
00:52:53,795 --> 00:52:55,630
<i>We'll see the autumn leaves in fall,</i>

890
00:52:56,131 --> 00:52:59,009
<i>and in winter,
it would be fun to go snowboarding.</i>

891
00:53:03,013 --> 00:53:04,014
[♪ music fades]

892
00:53:04,097 --> 00:53:05,891
- [engine revving]
- [navigator beeping]

893
00:53:09,728 --> 00:53:10,812
[breathing heavily]

894
00:53:10,896 --> 00:53:12,814
[♪ foreboding music playing]

895
00:53:14,274 --> 00:53:15,275
[grunts]

896
00:53:15,358 --> 00:53:18,445
- [high-pitched ringing]
- [grunts]

897
00:53:18,528 --> 00:53:20,030
[Hyeokchan] <i>Do you have any idea</i>
<i>what you've done?</i>

898
00:53:20,113 --> 00:53:22,115
- [Sujin] <i>You must've jumped at the chance.</i>
- [Haran] <i>I love you, Chan.</i>

899
00:53:22,199 --> 00:53:23,533
<i>Kang Hyeokchan.</i>

900
00:53:23,617 --> 00:53:24,951
<i>Did you have fun…</i>

901
00:53:25,952 --> 00:53:28,288
[grunts, exhales heavily]

902
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:32,250
[high-pitched ringing]

903
00:53:40,133 --> 00:53:41,134
[♪ music fades]

904
00:53:41,551 --> 00:53:43,386
[tires screech]

905
00:53:44,471 --> 00:53:46,473
[Chan breathing heavily]

906
00:53:47,849 --> 00:53:49,851
[♪ pensive music playing]

907
00:54:09,037 --> 00:54:12,666
HADONGDO-GIL

908
00:54:12,749 --> 00:54:14,751
[breathing heavily]

909
00:54:17,087 --> 00:54:18,171
<i>No…</i>

910
00:54:19,422 --> 00:54:20,423
<i>No…</i>

911
00:54:20,924 --> 00:54:22,217
<i>Please…</i>

912
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:24,594
[♪ dramatic music playing]

913
00:54:24,678 --> 00:54:25,845
<i>It can't be…</i>

914
00:54:26,429 --> 00:54:27,806
<i>No way…</i>

915
00:54:27,889 --> 00:54:28,890
<i>Please…</i>

916
00:54:30,308 --> 00:54:31,893
<i>There is no way I caused it.</i>

917
00:54:37,440 --> 00:54:38,942
[Haran crying]

918
00:54:47,367 --> 00:54:48,827
[Chan] <i>But what if I did?</i>

919
00:54:50,203 --> 00:54:51,288
<i>Then she…</i>

920
00:54:51,371 --> 00:54:52,789
[♪ music swells]

921
00:54:54,332 --> 00:54:56,334
[Haran bawling]

922
00:54:58,086 --> 00:55:00,088
[inaudible]

923
00:55:19,983 --> 00:55:22,402
- [♪ music fades]
- [PA beeps]

924
00:55:23,069 --> 00:55:25,071
[indistinct announcement on PA]

925
00:55:35,915 --> 00:55:37,208
[sighs]

926
00:55:39,002 --> 00:55:40,086
I wanted…

927
00:55:43,298 --> 00:55:45,008
to check something for the last time.

928
00:55:46,343 --> 00:55:47,886
Seven years ago…

929
00:55:47,969 --> 00:55:49,429
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

930
00:55:49,512 --> 00:55:50,764
…on the day of the accident.

931
00:55:52,640 --> 00:55:53,683
Did I…

932
00:55:55,769 --> 00:55:57,103
hit Kang Hyeokchan?

933
00:55:58,772 --> 00:56:01,983
Did I hit him and make him fall down?

934
00:56:03,360 --> 00:56:04,569
Is that why his lip tore

935
00:56:05,111 --> 00:56:06,821
and the waste container fell down?

936
00:56:11,159 --> 00:56:12,243
Is that true?

937
00:56:13,119 --> 00:56:14,120
Yes.

938
00:56:16,539 --> 00:56:18,124
You hit Hyeokchan.

939
00:56:21,753 --> 00:56:23,838
But why?

940
00:56:23,922 --> 00:56:24,923
[Sujin] Don't you remember?

941
00:56:25,006 --> 00:56:29,094
The day he came back from his trip,
you told Hyeokchan everything.

942
00:56:31,137 --> 00:56:32,138
[door closes]

943
00:56:34,432 --> 00:56:35,433
[♪ music fades]

944
00:56:35,517 --> 00:56:36,893
Long time no see.

945
00:56:37,477 --> 00:56:39,229
- Right.
- Hang on.

946
00:56:42,607 --> 00:56:46,319
[sighs] Sorry about this.
We need to switch laptops back.

947
00:56:46,403 --> 00:56:48,405
Move all your data from my laptop.

948
00:56:49,280 --> 00:56:50,281
Oh…

949
00:56:50,365 --> 00:56:51,366
Well…

950
00:56:52,325 --> 00:56:53,410
I…

951
00:56:53,493 --> 00:56:55,036
I have something to tell you.

952
00:56:56,162 --> 00:56:58,498
You do? What is it?

953
00:56:59,082 --> 00:57:00,333
{\an8}[Chan] Uh…

954
00:57:03,002 --> 00:57:04,838
While you were away, I--

955
00:57:04,921 --> 00:57:06,714
Will this take long?

956
00:57:07,966 --> 00:57:09,342
Yes, a bit.

957
00:57:09,426 --> 00:57:10,885
Then let's talk later.

958
00:57:10,969 --> 00:57:12,887
I have to meet my professor right now.

959
00:57:13,430 --> 00:57:15,014
I'll see you, uh…

960
00:57:15,849 --> 00:57:17,350
in the lab later.

961
00:57:22,939 --> 00:57:23,940
[sighs softly]

962
00:57:24,315 --> 00:57:25,859
Right. What is it?

963
00:57:26,443 --> 00:57:27,944
You needed to tell me something.

964
00:57:28,027 --> 00:57:29,195
Your messenger…

965
00:57:29,946 --> 00:57:31,114
What?

966
00:57:32,240 --> 00:57:34,117
While I was using your laptop,

967
00:57:34,993 --> 00:57:38,121
I kept chatting with your girlfriend.

968
00:57:42,792 --> 00:57:43,918
What?

969
00:57:44,002 --> 00:57:45,670
[♪ tense music playing]

970
00:57:45,753 --> 00:57:48,381
What are you talking about?
Say that again.

971
00:57:48,465 --> 00:57:49,924
We ended up

972
00:57:50,967 --> 00:57:52,343
chatting after that.

973
00:57:53,511 --> 00:57:56,014
But she thinks it was you.

974
00:57:57,724 --> 00:58:00,560
[chuckling] Hyeokchan,
you left your earphones in my car…

975
00:58:01,144 --> 00:58:02,187
[Hyeokchan] Are you saying

976
00:58:02,770 --> 00:58:05,356
you've been talking to Haran

977
00:58:06,232 --> 00:58:07,484
while I was away?

978
00:58:07,942 --> 00:58:08,943
Pretending to be me?

979
00:58:14,032 --> 00:58:15,658
Sorry. It's all my fault.

980
00:58:16,576 --> 00:58:17,577
[sighs]

981
00:58:19,078 --> 00:58:20,079
Hang on. [sighs]

982
00:58:21,748 --> 00:58:22,999
Who are you to do that?

983
00:58:23,875 --> 00:58:27,670
Why would you ruin everything like this?

984
00:58:28,254 --> 00:58:31,674
Tell me. What sort of things
have you been saying?

985
00:58:32,258 --> 00:58:33,259
Why?

986
00:58:33,343 --> 00:58:35,887
Did you think it was okay
since I asked you a few times?

987
00:58:35,970 --> 00:58:38,389
You were someone nobody even cared about.

988
00:58:39,724 --> 00:58:43,144
Did you get excited
that someone paid attention to you?

989
00:58:43,228 --> 00:58:44,812
[Chan grunts]

990
00:58:44,896 --> 00:58:46,856
- Kang Hyeokchan!
- [groans softly]

991
00:58:46,940 --> 00:58:50,860
[Sujin] <i>You had your eye</i>
<i>on Hyeokchan's girlfriend, Song Haran.</i>

992
00:58:51,819 --> 00:58:53,154
You told him

993
00:58:53,696 --> 00:58:56,824
that you'd been chatting with her
while he was traveling,

994
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:58,409
so things got heated.

995
00:58:59,118 --> 00:59:00,703
And you ended up hitting him.

996
00:59:00,787 --> 00:59:02,121
[breath trembling]

997
00:59:03,456 --> 00:59:06,626
Can you still say
you didn't have feelings for her then?

998
00:59:06,709 --> 00:59:08,711
[♪ dramatic music playing]

999
00:59:09,379 --> 00:59:10,421
Then…

1000
00:59:12,298 --> 00:59:14,884
[breath trembling] that accident…

1001
00:59:16,010 --> 00:59:18,221
Was it because of the container that fell?

1002
00:59:18,304 --> 00:59:20,306
[Sujin] Yes. So how do you feel?

1003
00:59:20,890 --> 00:59:23,351
Does it feel good to know the truth?

1004
00:59:25,603 --> 00:59:26,854
I told you,

1005
00:59:26,938 --> 00:59:29,357
nothing good would come
from digging up the past.

1006
00:59:34,070 --> 00:59:36,739
It was all because of you.

1007
00:59:37,824 --> 00:59:39,242
You caused the accident,

1008
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:42,287
and it killed Hyeokchan
and hurt a lot of people.

1009
00:59:49,127 --> 00:59:51,212
<i>Don't act like it's some grand love story.</i>

1010
00:59:51,296 --> 00:59:54,549
<i>You just tried to steal
Hyeokchan's girlfriend</i>

1011
00:59:54,632 --> 00:59:57,093
<i>and caused the accident that killed him.</i>

1012
00:59:57,176 --> 00:59:58,595
<i>That's all you are.</i>

1013
00:59:58,678 --> 01:00:00,096
[♪ music swells]

1014
01:00:02,307 --> 01:00:04,142
Do you have any idea what you've done?

1015
01:00:04,559 --> 01:00:06,227
I'm sorry. It's all my fault.

1016
01:00:09,814 --> 01:00:13,067
<i>It was all my fault.</i>

1017
01:00:19,907 --> 01:00:21,451
[♪ music fades]

1018
01:00:21,534 --> 01:00:24,412
Where in the world did you go?
You even left your phone behind.

1019
01:00:24,495 --> 01:00:26,873
You think I wouldn't worry
if you disappeared like that?

1020
01:00:29,042 --> 01:00:30,251
[Hayeong clicks tongue]

1021
01:00:31,711 --> 01:00:32,837
I was so worried.

1022
01:00:32,920 --> 01:00:35,089
You'd better not do that again.

1023
01:00:35,173 --> 01:00:36,966
I'm sorry for making you worry.

1024
01:00:38,718 --> 01:00:40,928
Ah. What about Chan?

1025
01:00:41,971 --> 01:00:43,931
Don't even mention him to me anymore.

1026
01:00:44,015 --> 01:00:46,893
I mean, didn't you meet him?

1027
01:00:47,518 --> 01:00:51,064
He heard you were gone
and started his car right away.

1028
01:00:51,147 --> 01:00:53,107
- Didn't you see him?
- What do you mean?

1029
01:00:53,191 --> 01:00:57,403
I called him late last night
because I didn't know where you were.

1030
01:00:57,487 --> 01:00:59,364
- I thought he might know.
- [sighs]

1031
01:00:59,447 --> 01:01:02,950
He said he knew where you could be
and left right away.

1032
01:01:03,534 --> 01:01:04,827
Maybe you missed each other.

1033
01:01:04,911 --> 01:01:06,996
Don't contact him about me anymore.

1034
01:01:07,664 --> 01:01:09,123
He has nothing to do with me.

1035
01:01:13,711 --> 01:01:15,213
His phone's off.

1036
01:01:17,840 --> 01:01:18,841
[sighs]

1037
01:01:20,593 --> 01:01:22,387
[Chan] <i>I couldn't react properly.</i>

1038
01:01:22,470 --> 01:01:24,138
- [car honk echoes]
- [high-pitched ringing]

1039
01:01:24,472 --> 01:01:26,599
<i>It's hard to tell
where sounds are coming from.</i>

1040
01:01:27,642 --> 01:01:28,643
[sighs]

1041
01:01:32,605 --> 01:01:34,357
What is it? Where are you going?

1042
01:01:35,400 --> 01:01:36,859
Where are you going?

1043
01:01:36,943 --> 01:01:39,237
This patient was transferred

1044
01:01:39,320 --> 01:01:41,906
after a lab explosion in Boston
seven years ago.

1045
01:01:41,989 --> 01:01:43,616
He was treated for full-body burns,

1046
01:01:43,700 --> 01:01:46,577
and shrapnel is still lodged deep
in the temporal bone.

1047
01:01:47,161 --> 01:01:50,456
It's a high-risk area, so we are only
monitoring it at the moment.

1048
01:01:50,540 --> 01:01:52,875
He also has unilateral hearing loss.

1049
01:01:52,959 --> 01:01:54,419
Burns? Shrapnel?

1050
01:01:54,502 --> 01:01:57,588
He visited the ER recently
after a brief loss of consciousness

1051
01:01:57,672 --> 01:01:59,090
and minor bleeding.

1052
01:01:59,173 --> 01:02:02,427
The outpatient clinic will check
if it's related to the shrapnel.

1053
01:02:02,510 --> 01:02:04,429
That really is a difficult spot.

1054
01:02:04,512 --> 01:02:05,555
[presenter] That's right.

1055
01:02:05,638 --> 01:02:08,224
If his bleeding
was caused by the shrapnel,

1056
01:02:08,307 --> 01:02:10,017
it may be accompanied

1057
01:02:10,101 --> 01:02:13,020
by neurological symptoms
such as auditory or visual hallucinations.

1058
01:02:13,104 --> 01:02:15,314
There have even been reports
of memory distortion

1059
01:02:15,398 --> 01:02:17,275
<i>in severe cases like this.</i>

1060
01:02:17,358 --> 01:02:19,485
[♪ pensive music playing]

1061
01:02:19,569 --> 01:02:22,113
The patient with the shrapnel
in the temporal bone…

1062
01:02:22,196 --> 01:02:23,364
Did he take the exam?

1063
01:02:23,948 --> 01:02:26,367
No, it's past his appointment,
but he hasn't shown up.

1064
01:02:27,910 --> 01:02:28,911
{\an8}But why do you ask?

1065
01:02:28,995 --> 01:02:30,121
{\an8}SEONU CHAN

1066
01:02:33,332 --> 01:02:34,459
It's nothing.

1067
01:02:34,959 --> 01:02:35,960
[♪ music fades]

1068
01:02:36,043 --> 01:02:37,378
Mr. Park.

1069
01:02:37,962 --> 01:02:39,547
Mr. Park, did you see…

1070
01:02:41,883 --> 01:02:42,884
[sighs]

1071
01:02:44,010 --> 01:02:46,012
[♪ soft emotional music playing]

1072
01:03:04,989 --> 01:03:06,199
[Chan] <i>A three-month trial!</i>

1073
01:03:06,282 --> 01:03:07,742
Just try me out as a free trial.

1074
01:03:07,825 --> 01:03:12,497
As soon as the three months are over,
I'll disappear without a trace.

1075
01:03:13,873 --> 01:03:15,124
[breathing heavily]

1076
01:03:19,879 --> 01:03:23,925
END OF TRIAL

1077
01:03:33,601 --> 01:03:34,602
[♪ music ends]

1078
01:03:36,270 --> 01:03:38,481
We can proceed
with the model fitting as revised.

1079
01:03:38,564 --> 01:03:40,066
[Raemee] Spring is here!

1080
01:03:40,149 --> 01:03:41,567
Spring is here!

1081
01:03:41,651 --> 01:03:42,819
Spring is here!

1082
01:03:42,902 --> 01:03:44,445
Look, spring is here.

1083
01:03:44,946 --> 01:03:47,782
- The forsythias have started blooming.
- [Hayeong gasps]

1084
01:03:48,241 --> 01:03:50,201
The forsythias are blooming?

1085
01:03:50,284 --> 01:03:52,411
That means we're on a tight schedule.

1086
01:03:52,495 --> 01:03:54,789
All right, let's hang in there
for a few more days.

1087
01:03:54,872 --> 01:03:55,998
- Let's do this!
- Let's do this!

1088
01:03:56,082 --> 01:03:58,835
- Let's do this!
- I'm so sleepy.

1089
01:03:58,918 --> 01:04:00,419
- [Sol chuckles]
- [Raemee] Goodness.

1090
01:04:00,503 --> 01:04:02,505
[pen scraping]

1091
01:04:05,341 --> 01:04:08,886
[Haran] <i>The seasons of life</i>
<i>don't come in order.</i>

1092
01:04:14,225 --> 01:04:15,226
[sighs softly]

1093
01:04:15,977 --> 01:04:17,436
It really is spring.

1094
01:04:20,481 --> 01:04:22,400
<i>Sometimes, when you think it's spring,</i>

1095
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:26,195
<i>winter suddenly arrives.</i>

1096
01:04:31,576 --> 01:04:32,577
<i>Take this.</i>

1097
01:04:33,369 --> 01:04:34,370
Oh…

1098
01:04:35,371 --> 01:04:36,747
Then let's do this.

1099
01:04:36,831 --> 01:04:38,624
It'll be like we're on a spring picnic.

1100
01:04:39,500 --> 01:04:40,501
Let's have fun.

1101
01:04:42,587 --> 01:04:43,671
[♪ soft emotional song playing]

1102
01:05:09,572 --> 01:05:12,325
SUMMER, SEVEN YEARS AGO
IT STARTED WITH WALLS

1103
01:05:15,411 --> 01:05:17,413
END OF TRIAL

1104
01:05:19,498 --> 01:05:21,459
[Haran] <i>The man</i>

1105
01:05:22,126 --> 01:05:24,587
<i>who suddenly lit up
my cold winter last year</i>

1106
01:05:24,670 --> 01:05:26,339
<i>like radiant spring sunlight…</i>

1107
01:05:27,381 --> 01:05:30,217
<i>disappeared from my life.</i>

1108
01:05:55,743 --> 01:05:57,453
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

1109
01:06:21,560 --> 01:06:23,688
{\an8}[Haran] <i>He disappeared.</i>

1110
01:06:23,771 --> 01:06:27,149
{\an8}<i>The Seonu Chan I know
would never leave like this.</i>

1111
01:06:27,733 --> 01:06:29,026
{\an8}[Sujin] <i>He disappeared because of me.</i>

1112
01:06:29,110 --> 01:06:31,320
{\an8}<i>- I did something I shouldn't have.</i>
- [bracelet clinks]

1113
01:06:31,404 --> 01:06:33,406
{\an8}He's been preparing for a long time.

1114
01:06:33,489 --> 01:06:36,492
{\an8}<i>It's gotten so bad
that there's nothing they can do.</i>

1115
01:06:36,575 --> 01:06:37,910
{\an8}- [Chan] <i>Do you remember…</i>
- [Haran cries]

1116
01:06:37,994 --> 01:06:41,664
{\an8}<i>…how I was trapped in winter for so long?</i>

1117
01:06:41,747 --> 01:06:43,582
{\an8}<i>I knew you'd understand</i>

1118
01:06:44,875 --> 01:06:46,460
{\an8}<i>my sincerity.</i>

1119
01:06:46,544 --> 01:06:48,629
{\an8}[Haran] <i>Seonu Chan, where are you?</i>

1120
01:06:48,713 --> 01:06:50,881
{\an8}Where on earth are you?

1121
01:06:53,968 --> 01:06:54,969
[♪ song fades]

1122
01:06:55,094 --> 01:06:57,096
[♪ theme music playing]

1123
01:07:02,935 --> 01:07:03,936
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

1124
01:07:04,020 --> 01:07:05,021
Translated by Juyoung Park

